ZEROPOINT — Deployment Guide
This guide provides exact steps to deploy ZEROPOINT with zero prior experience.
Option 1: GitHub Upload (Fastest — No Coding Required)
Step 1: Create GitHub Account
	1.	Go to https://github.com
	2.	Click “Sign up”
	3.	Create account (takes 2 minutes)
Step 2: Create Repository
	1.	Click green “New” button (top left)
	2.	Repository name: zeropoint-privacy-app
	3.	Select: Public
	4.	Check: “Add a README file”
	5.	Click “Create repository”
Step 3: Upload All Files
	1.	Click “Add file” → “Upload files”
	2.	Drag ALL files from the zeropoint-app folder:
	∙	App.js
	∙	package.json
	∙	app.json
	∙	babel.config.js
	∙	README.md
	∙	LICENSE
	∙	.gitignore
	3.	Commit message: “Initial release — ZEROPOINT v1.0.0”
	4.	Click “Commit changes”
Step 4: Enable GitHub Sponsors (Get Donations)
	1.	Go to your profile (top right)
	2.	Click “Sponsors”
	3.	Click “Join GitHub Sponsors”
	4.	Connect your bank account or PayPal
	5.	Set up sponsor tiers ($3, $10, $50 per month)
Done! Your repository is live at: github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/zeropoint-privacy-app
